name: DroneDetour
description: DroneDetour is a Java library and Android demo for UAV path planning and automatic detour navigation. It computes the shortest safe route around polygonal no-fly zones

name: Multi-Agent-Reinforcement-Learning-for-Drone-Delivery-and-Cooperative-Environments
description: This project explores Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) in two environments: a custom Drone Delivery system with no-fly zones and package coordination, and Simple Spread v3 (PettingZoo). We implement tabular (Q-Learning, SARSA, Double Q) and deep RL (DQN, Double DQN, Dueling DQN, QMIX) methods, comparing performance and strategies.

name: UAVproj
description: This project will develop a formal verification framework using Boolean Satisfiability Solvers (SAT solvers) to validate drone movement. By encoding movement constraints such as no-fly zones, collision avoidance, and altitude limits into logical expressions, a SAT solver will determine whether the given constraints are satisfiable.
